Abnormal tendon morphology

definition.value: A tendon (or sinew) is a tough band of fibrous connective tissue that usually connects muscle to bone and is capable of withstanding tension. Tendons are similar to ligaments and fascia as they are all made of collagen except that ligaments join one bone to another bone, and fascia connect muscles to other muscles. Tendons and muscles work together and can only exert a pulling force.

label.value: Hypertrophied muscle fibers

definition.value: The presence of an increased amount of muscle fibers with an increased diameter. This feature can be ascertained by microscopic examination of a muscle biopsy sample. Together with fiber size variation and atrophied muscle fibers, and hypertrophied muscle fibers are commonly found in myopathies.
Muscle hypertrophy can be assessed at the whole-muscle level (macroscopic methods) or the muscle fiber level (microscopic methods). This term refers to hypertrophy assessed at the microscopic level.
